properties.name: NSG Große Bree
properties.desc: Open cultural landscape north of Münster with wet meadows, hedges and small woods, important for farmland birds and species-rich grassland.

properties.name: NSG Emsaue
properties.desc: Alluvial meadows and floodplain habitats along the River Ems with pastures, oxbow structures and riparian woodland.

properties.name: NSG Vorbergs Hügel
properties.desc: Hilly landscape on the southern edge of Münster with species-rich dry and semi-dry grasslands, orchards and hedgerows.

properties.name: NSG Emsaue
properties.desc: Alluvial meadows and floodplain habitats along the River Ems with pastures, oxbow structures and riparian woodland.

properties.name: NSG Rieselfelder Münster
properties.desc: Internationally renowned wetland and bird sanctuary with basins, reed beds and observation hides, part of the European bird protection network.

properties.name: NSG Rottbusch
properties.desc: Forest and wet valley areas near the Ems with springs and small streams, offering habitat for amphibians and woodland species.

properties.name: NSG Huronensee
properties.desc: Small lake with surrounding woodland and reed belts, serving as a quiet refuge for waterfowl and dragonflies.

properties.name: NSG Alvingheide
properties.desc: Remnant heath and wet grassland with high groundwater levels and rare plant communities typical for the Münsterland.

properties.name: NSG Bonnenkamp
properties.desc: Moist lowland forest and meadow complex with old oak and ash trees, providing habitat for woodland birds and bats.

properties.name: NSG Wolbecker Tiergarten
properties.desc: Ancient oak-beech forest in the Wolbeck state forest with old-growth structures, deadwood and a dense path network.

properties.name: NSG Dabeckskamp
properties.desc: Small but diverse forest reserve with old deciduous stands and richly structured edges and clearings.

properties.name: NSG Gelmerheide
properties.desc: Former heath and dune landscape north-east of Münster with dry grassland, pine stands and open sandy areas.

properties.name: NSG Feuchtgebiet Handorf
properties.desc: Wetland mosaic of ditches, ponds and wet meadows near Handorf, important for amphibians and breeding birds.

properties.name: NSG Aa-Aue
properties.desc: Renaturalised floodplain along the Münstersche Aa with riparian woodland, near-natural river sections and floodplain meadows.

properties.name: NSG Davert (Münster)
properties.desc: Part of the large Davert forest and bog complex south of Münster with extensive beech woods and moor remnants.

properties.name: NSG Auwald Stapelskotten
properties.desc: Alluvial forest with ash and alder stands, wet depressions and near-natural streams near Stapelskotten.
